org.drip.param.definition

Class CreditNodeTweakParams

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.drip.service.stream.Serializer
      • org.drip.param.definition.NodeTweakParams
        • org.drip.param.definition.CreditNodeTweakParams

  • public class CreditNodeTweakParams
extends NodeTweakParams
    This class contains the place holder for the credit curve scenario tweak parameters, for a given measure, for either a specific curve node, or the entire curve (flat).

                      throws java.lang.Exception
        CreditNodeTweakParams constructor
        Parameters:
        strTweakParamType - Node Tweak Parameter Type
        strTweakMeasureType - Node Tweak Measure Type
        iTweakNode - Node to be tweaked - Set to NODE_FLAT_TWEAK for flat curve tweak
        bIsTweakProportional - True => Tweak is proportional, False => parallel
        dblTweakAmount - Amount to be tweaked - proportional tweaks are represented as percent, parallel tweaks are absolute numbers
        bSingleNodeCalib - Flat Calibration using a single node?
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception
